                "invention-title": [
                    "Iron ore concentrate coal-based hydrogen metallurgy rotary hearth furnace short-process steel making process",
                    "一种铁精矿煤基氢冶金转底炉短流程制钢工艺"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention discloses an iron ore concentrate coal-based hydrogen metallurgy rotary hearth furnace short-process steel making process which comprises the following steps: preparing coal-containing pellets from iron ore concentrate and high-volatile coal, and reducing iron oxide in a rotary hearth furnace mainly through full pyrolysis of the high-volatile coal and hydrogen produced by water gasification of carbon to prepare high-metallization-ratio pellets. The metallized pellets are subjected to neutral melt separation to obtain semi-molten steel and acidic steel slag, so that the steel production process flow is greatly shortened, flue gas emission is reduced, high-pollution process links such as sintering and coking are avoided, high-volatile-component and low-fixed-carbon coal is adopted as a reducing agent in the process, and carbon emission can be greatly reduced while the energy structure at the present stage of China is met."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明公开一种铁精矿煤基氢冶金转底炉短流程制钢工艺，该工艺采用铁精矿与高挥发分煤制备成含煤球团，在转底炉内主要通过高挥发分煤充分热解和水气化碳产出的氢气对铁氧化物进行还原，制备高金属化率球团，金属化球团经中性熔分后得到半钢水和酸性钢渣，大幅度缩短了钢铁生产工艺流程，减少了烟气排放，避开了烧结、焦化等高污染工艺环节，工艺采用高挥发分、低固定碳煤作为还原剂，符合我国现阶段能源结构的同时还可大幅度降低碳排放。"
                }
            ]
        }
